          "tz": 480
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Fan Yong",
          "email": "fan.yong@intel.com",
          "date": "2016-10-05 11:55:21.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "subject": "LU-8573 ptlrpc: cleanup bulks for ptlrpc_register_bulk failure",
        "message": "LU-8573 ptlrpc: cleanup bulks for ptlrpc_register_bulk failure\n\nIt is assumed that if ptlrpc_register_bulk() failed, then there\nshould be no bulk registered. But for the case of transferring\nmultiple bulks, it may be some bulks registered, but the others\nnot. Under such case, we need to cleanup the request environment\nvia ptlrpc_unregister_bulk() explicitly to avoid misguiding when\nre-try the request some time later.\n\nOn the other hand, for replay case, to be safe, we cleanup the\nrequest environment via ptlrpc_unregister_bulk() before sending\nout the replay request.\n\nMore sanity check about the bulk MDs in the ptlrpc logic.\n\nSigned-off-by: Fan Yong <fan.yong@intel.com>\nChange-Id: Ibc1063fdd614dcaf8671c5a3c6f820f8ade417d9\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
